<subSubSection id="98C489B69C6E8B21FF195FD1FEE35147" pageId="4" pageNumber="41" type="description">
<paragraph id="D061DA3D9C6E8B21FF195FD1FAE9513F" blockId="4.[151,1436,373,919]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="E2AA062F9C6E8B21FF195FD1FEB1528E" box="[197,369,413,438]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: Subgenital plates rather rounded laterally and caudally. Style with slightly curved slender apophysis with hair-like setae basally and stout setae apically, preapical lobe poorly developed. Aedeagus similar to previous species, but apex of shaft, with dorsal acute hook-like projection, in lateral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D061DA3D9C6E8B21FF195C59FB4B5117" blockId="4.[151,1436,373,919]" box="[197,1163,533,559]" pageId="4" pageNumber="41">
